				<wikidot:authorName>Ruengies_Elaj</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6193532</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><strong>Item #:</strong> SCP-XXXX-J</p> <p><strong>Object Class:</strong> Yesod<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-533480-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup></p> <p><strong>Special Containment Procedures:</strong> All Foundation personnel are to be subjugated to weekly baptizing, regardless of religious standing or lack thereof. If SCP-XXXX-J persists in a host after six months, a video reel of the subject's most humiliating failures is to be constructed and played continuously in their presence. This will not purge the host of SCP-XXXX-J, but it will make them feel like utter garbage.</p> <p>All documentation created by affected personnel are to be shredded, set on fire, and then peed on by their dog. <em>[Revised on ██-██-████].</em><br /> Due to the Foundation's increasingly short supply of dog urine, other animals may be used as well.</p> <p><strong>Description:</strong> SCP-XXXX-J is the designation for the Class-9 clusterfuck that is Foundation personnel and their sadistic obsession with reporting children's show characters as eldritch monstrosities in documentation form. SCP-XXXX-J was first discovered after a copypasta titled, <em>Thomas the World Engine, Lover to Trains and Blender of Infants</em>[sic], was forwarded to the O5 Council. The document had previously been spread solely among Level-4 staff via email, until Site Director ██████ accidentally hit &quot;send to all&quot; while trying to press &quot;send&quot; with his fat, cheetoh stained fingers.</p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-533480-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Hebrew for &quot;group of absolute degenerates&quot;</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
